## What I will not change yet

If after fix (1) the live windows still spawn fresh windows on each refresh (i.e. Bug 1 was
*literal* new windows, not just focus-raising), that's a different bug. Nothing in our code
creates figures inside the loop, so the hypothesis above is high-confidence — but if the symptom
survives, the next step would be a small reproducer that prints `len(plt.get_fignums())` each
refresh to confirm. Flagging here so it's not silently dropped.

